Package: stanflow
Title: An integrated Stan-based Bayesian Workflow
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Visruth", "Srimath Kandali", , "public@visruth.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-9097-0688")),
    person("tidyverse authors", role = "cph",
           comment = "Some code adapted from tidyverse package (MIT)")
  )
Description: Streamlines access to the Stan ecosystem by attaching core
    workflow packages, surfacing conflicts, and providing helpers to set
    up Stan interfaces with sensible defaults. Facilitates the Bayesian
    Workflow as described in Gelman et al. (2020)
    <https://arxiv.org/abs/2011.01808>.
License: BSD_3_clause + file LICENSE
URL: https://visruthsk.github.io/stanflow/
BugReports: https://github.com/VisruthSK/stanflow/issues/
Depends:
    R (>= 4.2.0)
Imports:
    bayesplot (>= 1.15.0),
    cli (>= 3.6.5),
    loo (>= 2.8.0),
    posterior (>= 1.6.0),
    projpred (>= 2.10.0),
    shinystan (>= 2.7.0)
Suggests:
    brms,
    cmdstanr,
    rstan,
    rstanarm,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Additional_repositories:
    https://community.r-multiverse.org,
    https://mc-stan-org.r-universe.dev
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Encoding: UTF-8
